\pard\plain \fi720\sl288\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Ayram, stricken with grief, knelt next to Elrahet\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s body. He picked up her cast off cowl and smoothed it in his hands. \u8220\'93You will not be forgotten,\u8221\'94 he said as he shrouded her flattened skull.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Elrahet\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s body was the foundation of a tableau }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 mourant}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1  which featured twenty something dead and dismembered Hrks, their body parts broadcast amongst an uncountable number of dead demons. Above it all was that slope of corpses half-spilled from of the Burshageet. All those people in that pile had suffered, too. They should not be forgotten. The two Hrks that Mandri had accidentally killed should not be forgotten. They were crumpled up and still smoking.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The sight of their upturned faces implanted a seed of shame in Mandri\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s chest. He wanted that feeling gone, but he\u8217\'92d killed those poor men. He didn\u8217\'92t mean to, he\u8217\'92d had no control, and they would have died anyways, but these thoughts didn\u8217\'92t help because it wasn\u8217\'92t their deaths which troubled him, it was the fact that he didn\u8217\'92t know their names. Like Elrahet, they deserved to be remembered. All these dead deserved remembering, and not just }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1\cf1 these}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1  dead; everyone who\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92d ever lived deserved remembering. Meanwhile, he\u8217\'92d spent his life curled up inside himself, as if none of that was true.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Now the shame was strong.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Even the demons deserved remembering. They had once been people.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Slate should not be forgotten.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Slate\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s hrkwhite cloak, wrapped around his belly, could not keep his blood from spilling out. His pallid skin was beaded with sweat. His gaunt expression drained into solemn horror as his eyes lost their focus. Barely alive, he prayed for help. He didn\u8217\'92t like what was happening to him.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Mandri wished Slate would be more direct. Slate should raise his voice and shout, \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You, my god, have made a mistake in killing me!\u8221\'94 It might be heretical, but why shouldn\u8217\'92t that poor man demand that he be set right? The world looked more interesting with his bravery in it.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Dear Solraheen, please consider stemming that fount of blood.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 And with the petition sent, Mandri demanded that it be heard. Solraheen must still be alive, not to answer the prayer, but to witness it. Because if there was no eternal audience to witness Slate\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s suffering, then what was the point? If that pain were to disappear forever, with no one to carry it on so that it could be transformed, then what was the point of it? There\u8217\'92d only be the suffering.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 That thought was bleak.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 It was too much.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 There had to be someone watching.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Mandri was watching. For the first time in his life he was truly paying attention, but he knew his limits. He was not enough.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Those Hrks still living didn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t care. Most busied themselves by cutting keepsakes off of dead demons. The red keenkedrin assassin was a valuable prize. Three Vessels huddled around its upper half, trying and failing to saw through the lizard\u8217\'92s neck with its own razored tail.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Pyetle, to his credit, tended to his wounded. One hurt Vessel had half a hag-beetle spike stuck straight through the meat of his thigh. Pyetle gave the man water, as well as an encouraging word, and the man\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s mood was immediatly lifted; he even thought to ask about Pyetle\u8217\'92s broken arm. Pyetle had it tucked inside his robe to keep it steady. Pyetle went to each of men like this, admiring their courage, sharing in their elation at being alive. \u8220\'93There\u8217\'92s meaning in it,\u8221\'94 he said to each of them. \u8220\'93Never forget that.\u8221\'94 Then he caught Mandri staring, and his Spark turned from a frantic pulse to a beating white. A glowing line danced out it. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Boy!\u8221\'94 he shouted.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Whether that line was fate, or purpose, or the Pyetle\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s raw will, Mandri couldn\u8217\'92t say, but it traced a true future. It ran straight out of the scribe to confront the spot where Mandri stood, and when Pyetle moved, he was drawn perfectly along its center.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Forgive me,\u8221\'94 Pyetle said as he approached. The pain of his broken arm elicited a slight wince, but did not dampen his excitement. \u8220\'93I hope you will forgive me. Sol\u8217\'92s light, there are a million things I want to say, and can hardly help saying them all at once.\u8221\'94 }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Ayram stood up from Elrahet\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s side. He swept his spud-bar spear to flick bits of beetle parts off its bloody haft. Some of these globs of landed right in front of Pyetle\u8217\'92s feet, suggesting he should stop.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Pyetle complied.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I apologize,\u8221\'94 Pyetle said, \u8220\'93for not appreciating your probity. It is a trait that I admire. You pokes have it, and I doubted it.\u8221\'94 He eyed Ayram warily. \u8220\'93I was also, at times, too aggressive in the application my duties. In my defense, I believe this whole situation warranted skepticism.  I might have encouraged you otherwise. As well, I did not know know that it was possible for a Mazid to summon their own fire. That is what happened, isn\u8217\'92t it?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Mandri confirmed it with a nod.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The light of Pyetle\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s Spark flickered.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Yes. Right. Well,\u8221\'94 Pyetle muttered. \u8220\'93As you have not yet scoured me and mine with your fire, I can assume that you do not wish us dead. I pray that mercy will endure. After all, a good number of my men did give their lives to defend you.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You don\u8217\'92t need to worry about me,\u8221\'94 Mandri replied. \u8220\'93\u8220\'93I\u8217\'92m almost afraid to breathe. My stomach feels like a hot pot with a shaking lid.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93What is your name?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Mandri.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Young Mandri,\u8221\'94 Pyetle repeated. He gave each syllable an unfamiliar weight, almost like respect. \u8220\'93Mandri, I am bound by oath to return you to the Lordship. Now, I recognize that I cannot force you to do anything you do not want to do. The only option open to me is to convince you to join me. That is, if you\u8217\'92ll grant me that opportunity. I think I could convince you, if you would grant me that opportunity.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Mandri stared blankly at the scintillating light in Pyetle\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s stomach.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1  \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93There\u8217\'92s been an incredible coincidence,\u8221\'94 Pyetle said. \u8220\'93Back there, I was about to die. My sword arm was indisposed when one of those roachy demons leaped for my face. I was certain I was about to die. I prayed for deliverance. Before that prayer was finished, your fire appeared and smote that demon out of the air. Now, if you kindled that fire absent a Minder, that alone would be a miracle. But the timing of it! It is a miracle of miracles. How can I not see the hand of Solraheen working in all of this? What are the odds?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Slim,\u8221\'94 Mandri said.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93This all coming after I\u8217\'92d sworn, on my life, to find you and keep you safe. It must }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1\cf1 mean}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1  something. White light, I have never felt so convicted. Look at me.\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94 Pyetle held out his good left hand. It was trembling. \u8220\'93I became a scribe out of a sense of duty, to give my life a fuller meaning. Now, here you are.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Ayram grunted. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93That\u8217\'92s a little much, don\u8217\'92t you think?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Pyetle\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s face flashed annoyance. Evidently, little of his new respect was reserved the giant. \u8220\'93I thought pokes were all sentimental,\u8221\'94 he said. \u8220\'93You must see something of the significance of what has happened here.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93What has happened, has happened.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Much more than that!\u8221\'94 Pyetle voiced. \u8220\'93This Mazid\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 excuse me, Mandri\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 he broke the boundaries of possibility. Because of him, we are alive! The beast is slain! What more could you want?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The chisel tip of Ayram\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s spear tinked against the floor. He grimaced as he leaned against it, then made a show of staring down all the dead bodies strewn about the chamber. First among them, Elrahet. Her ruin was so complete that one would be hard pressed to guess that there was actually a corpse underneath her black robes. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Pyetle bit his lip. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I know you pokes are unaccustomed to victory, but this is what victory feels like when it comes with a cost. Given the strength of the enemy, you should be happy to the pay the price.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The were a few discordant notes in Pyetle\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s rebuke, for they came on top of the sound of a man weeping. Mandri had assumed it was some wounded Vessel, but no, it was Moto. The Zosan was picking through the partial spill of the Burshageet\u8217\'92s stomach. Tears streamed down his face as he pulled a large demon fetus out of the pile. This fetus was connected to all the other bodies by some strange umbilical, and in pulling it out, he sent a slide of corroding bodies down to cover the spot he\u8217\'92d opened. Frustrated, sickened, and overwhelmed with despair, Moto collapsed to his knees.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93This was not a victory,\u8221\'94 Ayram grumbled.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I don\u8217\'92t agree,\u8221\'94 Pyetle said.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Have some respect!\u8221\'94 Moto scolded.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 He was speaking to two Hrks near him. In a bid to collect the Burshageet\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s head, they\u8217\'92d thrown a grappling hook up onto that small mountain of flesh and happened to snag the old king\u8217\'92s shoulder. They pulled the rope hard, and their grunting interrupted Moto\u8217\'92s breaking heart.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Moto, enraged, stood up.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The Hrks ignored him so completely that it seemed as if they didn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t notice him. They kept pulling, but the old king, with his green cloak and golden crown, would not roll over. His base was simply too large. Seeing the effort, a few excited vessels joined in. They pulled again, all together. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Moto drew his sword.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93She\u8217\'92s not dead!\u8221\'94 Mandri called.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Moto swiveled fast to face him. The man had clearly come to terms with Moteah\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s death, and his mourning was not to be toyed with.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Mandri cupped his voice. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I can feel her hand move in my stomach!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93What?\u8221\'94 Moto asked, incredulous.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The Hrks pulled again, straining hard. Two men pulling near the rope\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s heel turned the opposite way to engage their backs. A self appointed leader settled them into a repeating one-two-heave, as if they were playing tug of war with the dead demon king. The king\u8217\'92s skinny torso was not game, hooked as it was through the collar bone. Indeed, that body was nothing but a limp, bony extension of the rope. Mandri wondered what the Hrks hoped to accomplish, because it would be impossible to roll the whole beast over to fetch that old king\u8217\'92s golden crown. Then a horrible, bone-snap sounded out, followed by a ligament tear, and the peel of skin on which old king sat ripped out of its scarf of connective tissue. Drawn by the rope, it curled over.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The Vessel\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s stumbled against their sudden success. They regathered their feet and pulled again. This time the Burshageet\u8217\'92s flesh ripped easily, for the peel was pushed down from behind by the weight of bodies still trapped inside. A great swash of dead poured out. The tugging Vessels dropped the rope and scattered. They didn\u8217\'92t realize their victory until the old king\u8217\'92s green robe slapped against the floor, and his golden crown tumbled off his head.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I apologize,\u8221\'94 Pyetle remarked as he observed the ghastly scene. \u8220\'93I ordered them to use the hook. In my defense, I was expecting them to climb up to it, not pull it down. Though, I should have guessed that the beast\u8217\'92s flesh lacked integrity.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The men whooped in glee. But the moment they began to saw at the old king\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s neck, the whole mountain of bodies beside them dropped and tilted.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 An unseemly wet pop sounded out, and the peak of the pile of bodies sank into its center. After another wet pop, they sank at speed, a loud wet schlicking, their connected umbilicals dragging down the whole chain of bodies behind them, like a ship\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s anchor chain spooling out to sea. Yet another pop sounded, and the entire mound collapsed inward, then dropped a foot, then fell. It fell straight down, disappearing into a large black hole.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 All stood silent and amazed as a few stray mounds of umbilicaled bodies were yanked down into the abyss. Soon, all that was left of the Burshageet\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s inscrutable hunger was a great puddle of bile slicking the rim.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The Hrkan Vessels scrambled away from it, apparently concerned that the beast\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s stomach acid had corroded the floor and was liable weaken the fabled stone underneath their feet. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Interesting,\u8221\'94 Pyetle noted. Mandri noticed unfamiliar symbols etched around the chasm\u8217\'92s lip. The graven letters looked more like stab wounds than symbols. The light of the braziers illuminated them well, even as their grooves were mucked with filth.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Are we all sure,\u8221\'94 Pyetle said, \u8220\'93that you won\u8217\'92t let me convince you to visit me in Jeket? It is a much more inviting place than here, I assure you.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I think we should leave,\u8221\'94 Mandri asserted, even as he walked towards the dreadful hole to get a better look.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Stay back,\u8221\'94 Ayram warned. \u8220\'93That is a portal to Shis.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Is that what it says?\u8221\'94 Mandri asked, pointing to the graven letters.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Near enough,\u8221\'94 Pyetle answered. Confident but wary, the scribe joined Mandri at the abyss. \u8220\'93I can barely read Old Old Jandri, but I would wager a guess: it\u8217\'92s Schisol\u8217\'92s creed. Though, it has a less formal name\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 drivel.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93What does it say?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Nothing important. More vacuous words were never written. Here, poetic rambling. There, demonstrably wrong. Not worth our attention. My vote is with you, we should leave.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93What does it say?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93If you must know,\u8221\'94 Pyetle said as he shrugged;}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \tab \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Do not seek; if you are pure, you will find the truth.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \tab Do not obey; if you have found the truth, you will be in the right.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \tab Do not teach; if you are in the right, you will be followed.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \tab Do not enter unless you are followed.\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93That is the gist of it.\u8221\'94 Pyetle sighed in such a way as to make Mandri doubt his translation. \u8220\'93It is possible some of the nuance has eluded me, but it is as I said; drivel. The words are set against themselves. It orders us around, but also tells us to not obey. It\u8217\'92s not clever.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93It means,\u8221\'94 Ayram stated, \u8220\'93that to enter here, one must come with a willing sacrifice.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Is that right?\u8221\'94 Pyetle asked, though his tone suggested he already knew this. He peered into the hole. \u8220\'93I suppose that great demon counts as a sacrifice.\u8221\'94 He gave a half-hearted smile to show that he didn\u8217\'92t really mean it. \u8220\'93Why anyone would want to follow it is a mystery. It must be miles to the bottom.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93How much rope do you have?\u8221\'94 Moto asked.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Pyetle was caught so off guard by the question that he laughed. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You can\u8217\'92t possibly\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 \u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93If my sister is down there, I\u8217\'92m going down.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Good man, that way leads to death and Shis!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I\u8217\'92m not.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Mandri leaned over the abyss and peered into its depths. There was a light at the bottom of it.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Do you see that light?\u8221\'94 he said.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Moto, Pyetle, and Ayram stared after him. None of them appeared to notice anything. The lack of confirmation forced Mandri to realize what he was seeing was a distant Spark. It was rising fast.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 He shuffled back in fright.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93What is it?\u8221\'94 Pyetle asked.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Back up!\u8221\'94 Mandri \u8220\'93Step back!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 A thin dark blur flew up out of the hole, and like , and unfolded into the shape of a woman. Young, beautiful, with dark skin. Her graceful figure was provocatively draped in a flowing black satin sheet. The sheet\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s needle lace hem as she alighted upon the Black floor like an apparition.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Her glare, imperious. None other than Moteah.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Pyetle his sword.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Moteah drew a thin lipped smile.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Oh, please,\u8221\'94 she said to him. \u8220\'93Put your weapons away.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The rest of the Vessels recovered their wits and hurried themselves behind Mandri and the others.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Moteah\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s smile grew wider. Her white Spark glimmered nearer to gold as she fed on the fear emanating from this ball of sterner men. \u8220\'93Tongue tied?\u8221\'94 she asked as she lifted off the floor and glided towards them. She stopped at a respectful distance. \u8220\'93Do I frighten you? Speak, dear Mandri. This is your moment.\u8221\'94 }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Kill her,\u8221\'94 Ayram ordered.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Oh, kill yourself,\u8221\'94 Moteah snipped. \u8220\'93The world hardly needs another Spark telling others what to do. I should say the same to the rest of you.\u8221\'94 Her eyes lingered on Pyetle.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Moteah\u8230\'85\u8221\'94 Moto stammered. \u8220\'93What has happened?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You do not deserve to know,\u8221\'94 Moteah said sharply. \u8220\'93Your treatment of me was appalling. I can only imagine what Moteah\u8217\'92s life must have been like before I began to wear her face.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Moto quirked his head as if he hadn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t quite heard. He then took a step back, and Moteah pressed him further with a smile. And as each man puzzled out her meaning, her skin began to shift. Her smooth skin kneaded into wrinkles. Her dark skin a few shades lighter. Her black here shifted into silver. Her figure lengthened, her shoulders narrowed, and suddenly it was no longer Moteah floating there in front of them, but an old woman, still sheeted, alluring, relishing in the confounding surprise her sudden appearance.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I wonder,\u8221\'94 she said to Moto, voice severe as blight. \u8220\'93Can you reckon back to the day that I stole her place? You were so wrapped with dreams of the dead to notice how the girl who was still living had changed. Really, I shouldn\u8217\'92t complain that you never knew her. Your callousness made you easy to fool.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 She laughed a clear and happy laugh, while Moto floundered for want of a single word. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Oh, don\u8217\'92t be too hard on yourself,\u8221\'94 she said, \u8220\'93It wasn\u8217\'92t only you. Each of you have the same failing as every person who has ever lived; you simply do not care about other people. Isn\u8217\'92t that right, Mandri?\u8221\'94 }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Her eyes moved to Mandri. The the familiarity threw him completely off balance. Then came the sudden realization that Moteah was Lora and had always been for as long as he\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92d known her. And she was missing her hand. Lora, not Moteah, was missing her hand.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Where is she!?\u8221\'94 Moto yelled.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Lora sneered. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93It will be better for your peace of mind if you do not know.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Tell me! NOW!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Lora drew back in disgust. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Your desire to know is marked,\u8221\'94 she said as the black sheet fell off her shoulder. She caught it, then drew it back up. \u8220\'93Still, I will keep her story a secret, if only for my pleasure.\u8221\'94 }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93If you value consensus,\u8221\'94 Pyetle said aside to Mandri, \u8220\'93I agree with Ayram. You should kill her.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Again,\u8221\'94 Lora said, \u8220\'93Before you try killing other people, you might consider kill yourselves first.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Her face was hard as stone, impassive, judgmental. Mandri felt she was accusing him of something, staring at him like that.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93It\u8217\'92s your hand that squeezes my stomach?\u8221\'94 he asked, though he already knew the answer.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93It is,\u8221\'94 Lora said. She held out her nub of a wrist. \u8220\'93But do no let that stop you from doing what you came here to do. If you all wish to kill me, then I wish to see you try.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Can you stop me from using my fire?\u8221\'94 Mandri asked.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Why ask!?\u8221\'94 Moto whined. \u8220\'93Just do it!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Lora rolled her eyes. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Please,\u8221\'94 she chided. \u8220\'93Don\u8217\'92t bring me into this hurt you are feeling. This fear. You do it to yourselves. If you }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1\cf1 must}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1  blame someone else, blame Solraheen. Do we need a history lesson? Who put you in these frail and fearing bodies? It was Solraheen, children. You live, suffer, and die for His entertainment.\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93A beggar\u8217\'92s philosophy,\u8221\'94 Pyetle spat.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Is it?\u8221\'94 Lora asked, amused. \u8220\'93I suppose the truth would seem too simple to a man as smart as you. Don\u8217\'92t fret, I am not here to convince you of my beliefs. Belief is unnecessary. You will all find the truth, and peace, in the belly of the Burshageet.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I\u8217\'92ve killed your Burshageet,\u8221\'94 Mandri said proudly.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Lora deflected this triumph away with an upward twitch of her sharp chin. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93The true Burshageet will come,\u8221\'94 she said. \u8220\'93In fact, he stands now on my doorstep.\u8221\'94 An excited smile played on her lips.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Him?\u8221\'94 Pyetle asked, confused.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Me?\u8221\'94 Mandri echoed.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Lora\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s smile drew wide. \u8220\'93Why else would you be standing before me now?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Mandri\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s vanity welled up his chest, for in no possible world would he consent to looking as foul as that putrid beast. He raised his voice. \u8220\'93I\u8217\'92m here because you took my\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 \u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Oh, }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1\cf1 please}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 ,\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94 Lora sighed. \u8220\'93Whatever grievances you have are Mandrameen\u8217\'92s. Who is he to you? Naught but a fleshy vessel. Your entire being is a fiction which your Spark creates to distract from the misery of being alone. If you would jump with me into Shis, I could show you what I mean. You may bring your friends along.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 She drifted a bit to the side to give a clearer view of the abyss behind her.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Come, child. There is no need to hide.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Mandri assumed she was cajoling him to join her, but to his right, a pile of dead hag beetles stirred. Seb crawled out of it, covered in bettle guts and blood.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93My Lady!\u8221\'94 she screamed as she sprinted towards the witch. Once she\u8217\'92d gained a respectful distance, she fell to her knees and promptly smacked her forehead against the floor in supplication. Her whole body shivered.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You have performed wonderfully,\u8221\'94 Lora said softly. \u8220\'93You may do the honor of showing these poor fools what joy looks like.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Seb raised her head. It seemed she wanted desperately to say something important, but she hesitated, then wiped her tears, and smiled her wretched, black-tooth smile.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Go on,\u8221\'94 Lora said, reassuring. \u8220\'93Jump.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Seb stood up, cast a mournful look at Mandri and the others, then took off running towards the hole. When she got to the rim, she jumped.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Mandri felt something tug at his stomach.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Lora smirked.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Mandri looked down and saw a bright white thread of fate manifesting out of his very own Spark. It twirled past Lora\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s hip then leaped down into the abyss.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93No,\u8221\'94 said Mandri firmly. \u8220\'93I\u8217\'92m not going anywhere with you.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Lora\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s lips parted into a winsome smile.\u8220\'93Why else would you be here?\u8221\'94 she asked. \u8220\'93Mandrameen, the portrait painter. You\u8217\'92ve painted a thousand faces, and not one of them was true. How many self-portraits? Come, Mandri, you know how they never came out quite right. What was missing? A mirror never could show you. A mirror only made you more confused. It sold you the lie that you are here, alive, and always will be. Everyone else\u8217\'92s eyes close, and someday, yours might close forever, but who\u8217\'92s to say it\u8217\'92s not the world which disappears every time you blink?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93She\u8217\'92s deranged,\u8221\'94 Pyetle mumbled.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Mandri agreed, however, somewhere tucked inside Lora\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s babbling about blinking was the realization that he hadn\u8217\'92t blinked since he\u8217\'92d gone underground. Perhaps it had been longer. Perhaps he hadn\u8217\'92t blinked since the god-eye burgeon took hold of him. He began to worry that his eyes were stuck, and as he did, Lora locked her gaze with his.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 In a flash, her eyes shone gold, as if a shutter had opened and her Spark was declaring mystic tidings which he could not comprehend but could certainly feel\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 bright, and warm, and loving.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Do you sleep?\u8221\'94 she asked with interest. \u8220\'93What happens to Mandrameen when you sleep? Where does he go?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I\u8217\'92ve never thought about it.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Honesty is good,\u8221\'94 she said as her eyes dimmed. \u8220\'93Very good. Every self discovery begins with honesty.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Kill her already!\u8221\'94 Moto cried.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Lora was pleased to hear Moto\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s voice crack. \u8220\'93Look at this man,\u8221\'94 she said as she flicked her penetrating eyes over the strong-willed Zosan. \u8220\'93See how frightened he is. See that hate; he hates me. He hates himself. He is afraid of death. He hates his sister, too, but doesn\u8217\'92t know it. There is only one way for him to know peace, and it is the same for everyone: merge his Spark with yours.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Mandriii\u8230\'85\u8221\'94 Ayram growled.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93 \u8216\'91Mandri\u8217\'92 indeed,\u8221\'94 Lora said as she stepped aside to clear the path towards the gates of Shis. She held out an entreating arm. With the back of her hand, she brushed the thread of fate which led into the void. \u8220\'93Come, young Mandrameen. All those long years of wondering why no one ever saw in you what you saw yourself\u8230\'85come and let your eyes adjust to the darkness that you\u8217\'92ve been living in your entire life.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Mandri stood dumbstruck at the sight of that thread which foretold his future. He gasped when he realized that he\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92d taken a step forward.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Why dither?\u8221\'94 Lora said, amused. \u8220\'93Who do you think wrote your fate? All the gods are dead. There is no higher power weaving its will into our world.\u8221\'94 She stared down her long nose at Mandri. \u8220\'93This thread you follow is your own. }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1\cf1 You}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1  put it there, no one else. Here, I\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92ll make it clearer for you.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Her long fingers stretched up into the air and snatched a Black knife out of nothingness. She set this blade against Mandri\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s fate and neatly plucked it. In an instant, his bright worldline popped into shimmering dust.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Now,\u8221\'94 she said, \u8220\'93given that I\u8217\'92ve both invited you in and denied that inevitable future, what is it that you think I want you to do?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Mandri did not know. And more, he feared that whatever he was going to do would play right into her hands. This witch, and her ancient eyes, had seen much more of the future than he.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 What }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1\cf1 did}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1  she want him to do?}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 He desperately wanted to know. He couldn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t escape the situation by doing nothing at all, because that, perhaps, was precisely what she wanted him to do. Most likely, given context, she wanted him to take her ramblings seriously. She wanted him to actually entertain the absurd idea that his existence was a fantasy, that \u8216\'91Mandrameen\u8217\'92 was nothing but a label stapled onto a bag of impertinent opinions, prejudices, and obediences, those symptoms of stressed out flesh, and what a stress it was, meat snagging on time, stretching out the years. Yes, his Spark did not belong to this weight. If he had any sense, he would lay down and die, for in death there is tunnel of light drawing to a point of critical masslessness where the immeasurable joy of infinity explodes forever.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Lora was staring at him with her golden eyes.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 She was channeling these thoughts into him.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Mandri fought back with a scowl. He made certain that she could feel his purpose. Feel it she did, for her brows jumped as she burst into a tremendous fit of laughter.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Oh, my, my!\u8221\'94 she said. \u8220\'93Such a mood is unbecoming! You make it seem like you wish to fight.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I do.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93My dear boy, me and mine have collected an uncountable number of Sparks throughout the ages. Yours would be no different.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Of that number,\u8221\'94 Mandri marked, \u8220\'93how many belonged to a Mazid?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Please,\u8221\'94 Lora said with annealing charm. \u8220\'93We have collected the Sparks of gods. There is no hope of defeating me. You are always welcome to try\u8230\'85if that is what you }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1\cf1 truly}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1  want.\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Very well,\u8221\'94 said Mandri, and when next he opened his mouth, his throat ran gold with fire. Out poured a beam as bright as the sun. It roared through the air and smashed into the empty dark. It would have rubbed Lora\u8217\'92s head right off her neck if she hadn\u8217\'92t flown away in a blur. Her sudden flight traced a loop and a swirl before ending in a dramatic glide as she alighted right back down in the spot where she\u8217\'92d been. The sheet that was her robe billowed down to recover her naked figure, as did her hair, for her flight had loosed her silver locks. They hung now upon her shoulders.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93What is it you are trying to defeat?\u8221\'94 she asked.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Mandri thought this was obvious, but somehow his silence was not the answer she was hoping for. She sighed deeply. Her golden eyes were gone, revealing a tiredness like any other.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Are you fighting evil? Is that it? Hate?\u8221\'94 She motioned to the abyss behind her. \u8220\'93Do you think that pit is despair? My dear boy, both love and hate are symptoms of the same corruption. You fight to keep our Sparks apart. I fight to join them. The basic conflict here, as it is in all things, is separation. The only cure to all your fear and suffering is union.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Is that what you and yours are doing when you kill? Committing to union? Seems like a permanent separation to me.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93We do not kill. We consume.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93And I\u8217\'92ll have no part of it.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You have no choice. Now that your Spark is burning, you will need to eat. I am only asking you to eat for a greater purpose. Fight the cravings if you must, but know that you do not have the power to frustrate the collapse of this world. None of you do. If I would die today, it would change nothing.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Put that to the test.\u8221\'94 Ayram grumbled.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Oh, but I will,\u8221\'94 Lora said. She raised her black knife up high. \u8220\'93My labors are over. I am more than willing to lead by example.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 She plunged her blade into the left side of her belly, just under her ribs. Straining, she sliced across to the right. Blood poured over her fingers as she pushed the blade deeper. She moaned, doubled over, and trembled violently. Her hair fell around her face. Her arms curled inward, shielding the wound, as though embarrassed of her agony. Her shoulders heaved as she continued to cut until blood splashed out onto the ground. Finally, she straightened up. She held out her squirming stomach. A length of intestine dangled from it, swinging like a rope over the blood-slicked chasm in her abdomen.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You can have me,\u8221\'94 she said as she presented the seat of her Spark for all to see. The Spark itself was a drifting daub of white light. Mandri was stupefied by the sight of it.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Lora\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s haggard breathing was wet with sips and spits of blood. She struggled to throw her voice. \u8220\'93If not you, it may be that a gentler Spark will claim it!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 She faltered, then nearly collapsed into the growing puddle of her own blood. Her determination willed her back upright. In defiance of her pain, she held her stomach up higher for all to see.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Then the abyss behind her sniffed it.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Mandri thought this was a hallucination, but the lace hem of Lora\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s sheeted robe listed backwards. The pools of bile around the hole\u8217\'92s rim rippled. And as Mandri wondered what great thing could shift this air, there came another inhale so strong that he nearly lost his footing. He braced himself for a stronger pull, but silence followed. And as he adjusted to the fear of being sucked into that hole against his will, that black portal breathed out a sleepy stream of smoke.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The smoke curled up high, then reached down, towards Lora. A sneaking tendril surged out to taste the stomach held in her hand.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Spears up!\u8217\'92 Pyetle shouted. His small company raised theirs spears, and surprisingly, this caused that finger of smoke to recoil. It hovered in the air, as if considering them and their intentions. Then it bolted upwards, speeding, until it smacked into the distant ceiling and bloomed into a cloud of shadow. This soft explosion sent curls of smoke spiraling out, some landing the hanging braziers, quieting their fires. Soon, the only light still burning was a single Hrkan torch.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Out of this darkness came the pinching laughter of demons. Not just two, or three, or twenty, there were enough raving voices to split the ear. And on their cue, thousands of blinking, torch-reflecting eyes opened\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 eyes set wide, bovine eyes, mousey eyes, the saucer eyes of squid, fourfold sets of spider eyes swaying overhead. Every kind of eye in all creation swirled around inside this enveloping darkness. But they were not keen on Mandri, or the Vessels. They sought Lora\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s proffered Spark.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 To Mandri\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s left, a blue-Sparked demon stepped out of the smoke. It looked like a naked, knuckle-walking monkey, vaguely human and similar in size, with its lips stuffed up its nose. To his right, another set of glowing eyes stepped forth, bearing a brownish Spark; this was a giant river rat wearing the body of a bubble-backed ox with a roanish hide. These two were joined by a herd of grotesqueries, each leaping out, it seemed, from nightmares. A snake man, a crab stoat, a wolf crow, a fish woman; they each loomed large, snarled, and licked their teeth. The fish had a much harder time without a muscular tongue, or teeth, but it certainly tried as it assumed its spot in the encirclement of Mandri\u8217\'92s party. Behind these beasts, the great wall of smoke compacted into a panoply of miscreants, each as different as the next. Out of their Sparks spooled threads of hungry purpose. They stretched out and latched fast to Lora\u8217\'92s stomach. Each attachment elicited a growl, hiss, or roar, and soon the air was alive with teeth chatter, giggle chatter, yapping, sucking, squealing chatter.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1  When this maddening chorus peaked, Lora tossed her stomach towards Mandrameen.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 That stomach bounced near  Mandri\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s feet, dragging its net of hunger along with it.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Lora, a spectacle of death, fell to the ground. On hand and knees, she coughed a spurt of blood, then cried out, \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93FEAST!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The crowd of snarling, seething demons took a step towards her stomach. The torchlight didn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t show that many, but the dark behind their shoulders was bright with a sprawling rainbow of Sparks. White lines spelling out hunger attached to Mandri and his companions. It seemed that any fresh Spark would do.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93We can do this,\u8221\'94 Pyetle said, though his own unsteady voice seemed to doubt it. \u8220\'93We can survive this. If Mandri spreads his fire wide, and we duck low and\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 \u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The hunting shriek of a winged demon disagreed. And this demon was the most grotesque yet\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 bat-winged and the size of a child, with a little boy\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s flat face. Enormous funnel ears framed its lidless, pea-sized eyes. It swooped down, stretched its legs, and splayed its talons wide. But it did not shriek again, for its small head was wooshed away by a burst of Mandri\u8217\'92s flame. The heat was so intense that the bat-child\u8217\'92s body burst into a shower of gore. Its blood rained down on the demon host. Then all of Shis broke loose.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Every kind of creature imaginable ran, hopped, slithered, stomped, galloped towards him and his. Scales sparkled and muscles bulged. Long snouts snapped. Fanged maws hissed. Sharp beaks screamed for oblivion. Mandri\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s golden fire screamed back.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 One great sweeping arc of his coruscating heat cut the first rank of demons out at the waist. Those that scurried underneath his sweeping flame\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 the dog, hog, and lizard demons, the hag beetle demons\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 these he dispatched with incredible precision and blinding speed as more than twenty beams of fire flared out of his mouth in space of a short-held breath. Every smoking corpse burst into flame, leaving a ring of sizzling flesh to serve as stumbling blocks to the rest of the onrushing horde. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Ayram, Moto and the others crouched close. Some Vessels lay flat on the floor as his fire spiraled round and round. At each turn, his flame traveled further out, mowing down larger swathes of demons. A smattering of explosions peppered the dark as those who tumbled out of the air boiled in their juices and combusted on collision with the ground. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Still the demons came.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Hunger twisted their faces.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The swarms of Shis were pouring forth to eat. Their rippling, chitinous, feathered backs glinted against the flames. The very skin of the cavern rock was writhing. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 There were too many. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Some had escaped his notice.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Moto struggled to fend off the claws of a great horned viper. Ayram dodged and countered a spiraling stinger which sprouted out of the head of a duck-billed horse. Pyetle\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s leg was caught in the froggy maw of a giant man-stork, even as one of his Vessels hacked at its neck.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93This is hopeless!\u8221\'94 Pyetle cried as he regained his foot.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93We need to run!\u8221\'94 Ayram shouted. He stabbed a giant fly that shat out silk like a worm.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Run where?!\u8221\'94 Moto wailed. \u8220\'93We\u8217\'92re surrounded!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Mandri heard all this and cleared a path back to the constricting tunnel from which they\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92d come.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Go!\u8221\'94 Ayram thundered, and on they went, with Mandri leading the way. He hopped over flailing tail and claw, burning a bright hole into a giant stomping snake. Ayram took up the rear, swinging his great spear, unbuckling a ratbird\u8217\'92s ribs from its slinking spine.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1  Something wet pricked pricked Mandri\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s cheek. He looked up and saw a scattering of raindrops glittering amongst the swarm of Sparks above. Another drop of wet pricked his forehead.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 This was not rain; the demons above were pissing in excitement.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Ayram grabbed the neck of his robe, snarled, and threw him onward.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Move, you idiot!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 There were too many.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 He harassed all their pursuers with his flame, but there were too many. They were quick. He ran into the tunnel, but demons were already in it. They would be overwhelmed no matter which way they fled. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Here!\u8221\'94 he shouted in between gasps of fire, hoping the others understood that this tunnel was where he wanted to make a stand.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 He spun around to burn their pursuers but was instantly blinded by a flood of white light; every filament of hungry purpose was drawn into tube rock. He screamed against it, and though he slaughtered many, it was not enough to poke the simplest hole in that vast field of white. He swept his arc around in circles, tracing what he thought was the tunnel\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s , but even so he could hear the ravenous swarm closing in.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Ayram\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s massive fingers grabbed his own.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 They pressed something into his palm.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 A handle.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 A knife.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Mandri\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s fingers felt the knapped back of the blade with dawning awe\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 it was Elrahet\u8217\'92s shard of Fabled Black. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 He gripped it, and swung. Thick bundles of fibrous purpose poofed into mist. Demons collapsed mid-pounce. One squealing pig-bug even crashed into him, but did not bite. A nearby Vessel stabbed it, pushed it away, and Mandri kept cutting fate. He sliced and cut until not a single strand was left.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Mandri paused to catch his breath.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 His companions were hunched down against the rock beside him, surprised as ever to be alive. They stared up at him like a fresh-licked litter of pups. Their Sparks still shone brightly.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Are there more?\u8221\'94 Pyetle wondered. \u8220\'93There must be more, but I can\u8217\'92t hear any.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Oh, there\u8217\'92s more,\u8221\'94 Mandri said.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93What are they doing?\u8221\'94 Pyetle wondered. The scribe ventured back down the tunnel, where the walls were plastered with steaming demon gunk. Beyond, in the comet\u8217\'92s chamber, a smattering of corpse-fires smoldered bright.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Pyetle,\u8221\'94 Mandri said, \u8220\'93Please step back.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Pyetle did as told.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Mandri watched in horror as new lines of hunger stretched out of innumerable demon Sparks. This time they attached to whichever Spark was nearest; that being each other. The hunger spread in ever direction, until the floor, walls, and ceiling of the god-killing stone was layered in net of snarling beasts.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Somewhere in the distance, a cat yowled.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 A goat bleated in fright.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 An warbling shriek was quickly snuffed out.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Silence regained the chamber.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Then demonic host fell upon itself to feast.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 For lack of light, the carnage could only heard. A cacophony of pained yelps and feral . The only detail Mandri could gather from that simmering sea of Sparks was that, if any demon stopped to eat, its own flesh was torn.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 He had to summon his fire a few more times to deal with whatever death-rattle battles splashed into his tunnel. Mostly, the demons were content to ravage each other. His fight was effectively over.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 So, why was he was still afraid?}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 He noticed Lora\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s Sparked stomach hanging hanging against Ayram\u8217\'92s chest like a bloody pendant. Ayram had its thin tail cinched between his teeth. He\u8217\'92d stolen the thing, for some godforsaken reason.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Mandri quickly looked away, hoping the giant didn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t sense his pang of hunger.}}